21 Laps娱乐公司

7
00:00:44,700 --> 00:00:47,580
{\an8}制作公司
原子怪兽影业

8
00:00:48,660 --> 00:00:51,530
{\an8}制作公司
福波斯

9
00:00:52,610 --> 00:00:55,710
{\an8}原创译制
蒙太奇字幕组

10
00:00:59,900 --> 00:01:04,260
{\an8}（异步研究所）

11
00:01:06,950 --> 00:01:10,450
{\an8}（基洛纳区调查：档案446 — 纳伦·沃恩
1990年6月19日
美国能源部）

12
00:01:22,380 --> 00:01:24,280
Okay, okay, okay, okay...
好 好 好

13
00:01:26,730 --> 00:01:28,400
Okay...
没事的

14
00:02:04,770 --> 00:02:06,820
Yes... Yes...
对 对

15
00:02:06,840 --> 00:02:11,050
Yes, yes, come on... Come on, yes! Yes, yes!
对 对 快点 快点 没错 没错

16
00:02:11,060 --> 00:02:12,900
Okay. Okay. Okay.
到了 到了 到了

17
00:02:52,490 --> 00:02:54,470
Here we go, here we go.
找到了 找到了

18
00:02:54,610 --> 00:02:57,240
Okay. Okay. Fuck.
好 好 该死

19
00:02:57,350 --> 00:03:00,160
Work. Work. Work.
能用 能用 一定得能用

20
00:03:01,340 --> 00:03:03,720
Standard... Okay...
基准组... 好...

21
00:03:03,740 --> 00:03:05,940
Standard, can you- can you hear me?
基准组 你们...你们能收到吗？

22
00:03:06,330 --> 00:03:08,030
This is Naren.
我是纳伦

23
00:03:08,050 --> 00:03:09,360
And I've, um...
我 呃...

24
00:03:09,380 --> 00:03:11,490
I've been separated, uh, from the others.
我跟其他人走散了

25
00:03:11,510 --> 00:03:12,610
And I think I'm okay,
我应该没事

26
00:03:12,630 --> 00:03:13,840
but I'm not sure where I, uh...
我不知道我现在到底在哪儿

27
00:03:14,680 --> 00:03:17,210
I've never been out this far before, so I don't...
我从来没走到过这么深 所以我也...

28
00:03:18,950 --> 00:03:20,280
There was this, uh...
刚才有个...

29
00:03:20,290 --> 00:03:22,940
I didn't get a good look at it, but there was, um...
我没看清 可是 呃...

30
00:03:23,130 --> 00:03:25,010
there's something else in here.
这里还有别的东西

31
00:03:26,810 --> 00:03:28,240
I need you guys.
你们快来

32
00:03:28,700 --> 00:03:31,190
Okay? I need you guys to get me, please.
明白吗？快来接我 求你们了

33
00:03:32,200 --> 00:03:35,030
Fuck, I need you guys to come out and get me.
该死 快来把我弄出去

34
00:03:35,040 --> 00:03:37,250
Can you... can you come, please, standard?
麻烦来接我 求你们了 基准组

35
00:03:38,050 --> 00:03:39,780
Standard?
收到了吗？

36
00:03:40,600 --> 00:03:42,040
Oh, fuck!
完了

37
00:03:46,340 --> 00:03:47,670
Fuck...
完了

38
00:03:55,080 --> 00:03:56,650
Fuck! Fuck...
该死 该死

39
00:04:08,690 --> 00:04:10,290
Oh, shit... What the fuck?
该死 搞什么鬼？

40
00:05:14,010 --> 00:05:17,190
{\an8}（需无用信...）

41
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:43,710
What the fuck?
怎么回事？

42
00:06:07,910 --> 00:06:09,680
Fuck! Fuck! Fuck!
完了 完了 完了

43
00:06:13,940 --> 00:06:15,220
Shit.
该死

44
00:06:15,470 --> 00:06:16,600
Fuck!
完了

45
00:06:21,110 --> 00:06:22,890
Fuck, fuck, fuck! Fuck!
不 不 完了 完了

46
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:55,090
{\an8}《后室》

47
00:07:22,950 --> 00:07:33,660
{\an8}（山脊公寓楼盘）

48
00:07:49,210 --> 00:07:53,110
We all have our loops, our habits...
谁都有自己的死循环 甩不掉的习惯...

49
00:07:55,530 --> 00:07:58,190
...behaviors that keep us walking in circles...
我们总是重蹈覆辙...

50
00:08:00,160 --> 00:08:03,200
...reaching for the same solutions over and over again,
一遍遍地尝试老路

51
00:08:05,370 --> 00:08:12,900
{\an8}（克船长的家具帝国）

52
00:08:06,260 --> 00:08:09,320
thinking each time they'll take you somewhere new.
却指望能走出一条新路

53
00:08:10,130 --> 00:08:11,290
But they don't.
但没用

54
00:08:18,770 --> 00:08:20,010
And still,
毕竟

55
00:08:20,030 --> 00:08:23,290
it's the neural pathway of least resistance.
神经回路总是走阻力最小的路

56
00:08:23,300 --> 00:08:25,750
{\an8}（奸商）

57
00:08:25,760 --> 00:08:28,150
A path you made.
你给自己铺了一条小路

58
00:08:28,160 --> 00:08:31,310
It's the one that kept you safe when you were a child.
小时候 这条路保护了你

59
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:39,020
{\an8}（全店促销 低价保证 一件不留 全场甩卖）

60
00:08:36,670 --> 00:08:39,020
You learned to push people away
你学会了在被伤害之前

61
00:08:39,210 --> 00:08:41,140
before they could hurt you.
抢先一步把别人推开

62
00:08:42,910 --> 00:08:44,100
And now,
但现在

63
00:08:44,110 --> 00:08:45,380
as an adult,
你成年了

64
00:08:44,110 --> 00:08:46,690
{\an8}（逾期通知）

65
00:08:45,390 --> 00:08:47,560
you're still stuck right where you started.
你依然留在原地

66
00:08:53,290 --> 00:08:54,460
Alone.
唯独你一人

67
00:09:00,620 --> 00:09:02,120
I mean, I'm not lonely.
我有人陪啊

68
00:09:03,070 --> 00:09:07,440
I have employees and... customers.
我有店员 还有顾客

69
00:09:07,460 --> 00:09:10,220
I didn't say lonely. I said alone.
我没说有人陪 我说的是唯独你一人

70
00:09:11,090 --> 00:09:12,550
Yeah, well, I mean...
好吧 是 但是...

71
00:09:14,380 --> 00:09:16,080
I hurt people.
我老是伤人

72
00:09:16,090 --> 00:09:17,940
I don't want to. It's just the way I'm wired.
我也不想 可我脑回路就是这样接的

73
00:09:17,950 --> 00:09:20,110
So maybe I deserve to be alone.
可能就该把自己关起来

74
00:09:20,800 --> 00:09:22,990
Do you think anyone deserves to be alone?
谁活该把自己关着吗？

75
00:09:24,090 --> 00:09:25,930
I don't know, but, you know,
我说不好 但怎么说呢

76
00:09:25,950 --> 00:09:27,390
maybe it's not such a bad thing.
也许这样也挺好

77
00:09:28,550 --> 00:09:30,490
Being alone feels...
自我封闭...

78
00:09:30,500 --> 00:09:31,730
deeply ingrained.
已经刻进骨子里了

79
00:09:32,050 --> 00:09:33,380
I understand.
我理解

80
00:09:34,110 --> 00:09:37,340
You've had dreams and a lot of resistance,
你有梦想 但老是受挫

81
00:09:37,360 --> 00:09:40,490
not a lot of support in realizing those dreams.
身边也没人支持你

82
00:09:41,010 --> 00:09:43,680
And when we've experienced...
当伤害变成了...

83
00:09:44,410 --> 00:09:47,180
hurt again and again,
一次次家常便饭

84
00:09:47,700 --> 00:09:49,040
we start to expect it.
你就会习惯性地想

85
00:09:49,050 --> 00:09:50,610
It's like, "Oh, I know this path.
“哦 这路我熟”

86
00:09:50,620 --> 00:09:52,310
I know where it goes."
“下场一定是一样的”

87
00:09:53,580 --> 00:09:54,850
So...
所以...

88
00:09:55,470 --> 00:09:58,110
are you interested in forging a new path
你想不想摆脱这个死循环

89
00:09:58,120 --> 00:09:59,870
and see where that leads?
走出一条不同的路？

90
00:09:59,960 --> 00:10:01,400
Sure.
好啊

91
00:10:01,570 --> 00:10:03,440
Why not? You know, I'm here.
我来都来了 就试试吧

92
00:10:04,070 --> 00:10:05,270
Great.
很好

93
00:10:05,580 --> 00:10:07,380
So I want to revisit
要不咱们重温一下...

94
00:10:07,390 --> 00:10:09,590
an exercise we've done before.
之前练过的那个...

95
00:10:10,860 --> 00:10:11,790
The role play.
角色扮演

96
00:10:11,800 --> 00:10:13,450
- Oh, the acting thing? - Yeah.
- 哦 演戏那套？ - 对

97
00:10:13,460 --> 00:10:15,430
- I feel stupid doing that. - I know.
- 我觉得太丢人了 - 我懂

98
00:10:15,540 --> 00:10:17,510
But we have a few minutes. Let's, um...
但既然还有点时间 就....

99
00:10:18,880 --> 00:10:20,520
Yeah, let's try. A little bit.
试一下吧 稍微试试

100
00:10:21,080 --> 00:10:22,510
All right.
好吧

101
00:10:23,150 --> 00:10:24,490
Let's set the scene.
咱们先定个场景

102
00:10:25,440 --> 00:10:29,560
Let's go back to the night that Barbara left you.
回到芭芭拉离开你的那晚

103
00:10:30,680 --> 00:10:33,680
You mean the night she kicked me out of my own house?
你是说她把我从我自己家给撵出去的那晚？

104
00:10:33,690 --> 00:10:35,390
Yeah.
对

105
00:10:35,720 --> 00:10:37,320
I'm playing myself.
我演我自己

106
00:10:37,340 --> 00:10:38,380
And I'll be Barbara.
我演芭芭拉

107
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:40,190
It is my house, by the way.
别忘了 那可是我的房子

108
00:10:40,860 --> 00:10:42,650
I'm the one paying for it.
房贷都是我在还

109
00:10:42,780 --> 00:10:45,020
- I know. - All right.
- 我知道 - 好吧

110
00:10:47,800 --> 00:10:49,910
Okay, so, um...
好 那...

111
00:10:50,910 --> 00:10:53,560
I got home late. I don't know how late.
那天我回家晚了 具体几点我忘了

112
00:10:53,920 --> 00:10:55,820
Uh... She was already asleep. Maybe midnight.
那时候她已经睡了 应该是半夜了

113
00:10:56,800 --> 00:10:58,750
She usually goes to bed before... It doesn't matter.
她一般睡得早... 算了 这不重要

114
00:10:58,760 --> 00:11:01,610
The point is, I was in the kitchen, and, um...
重点是我当时在厨房 额...

115
00:11:01,630 --> 00:11:04,130
the glass, I broke the glass, and...
有个杯子 我把杯子打碎了

116
00:11:04,390 --> 00:11:07,860
she comes running down to see what happened, and...
她听见动静跑下来 然后...

117
00:11:08,460 --> 00:11:09,880
things escalated.
就闹起来了

118
00:11:09,890 --> 00:11:11,330
And how do you feel?
那你当时什么感受？

119
00:11:12,370 --> 00:11:13,870
Well, I was...
我当时...

120
00:11:13,880 --> 00:11:16,600
I was drunk, and, um...
我当时喝多了...

121
00:11:16,650 --> 00:11:18,810
I-I felt stupid, you know.
我 我觉得自己挺蠢的 你懂吧

122
00:11:18,830 --> 00:11:21,830
I was angry, because... because I broke the glass.
我就火了 因为...因为我把杯子打碎了

123
00:11:21,840 --> 00:11:23,450
Can you say that to me?
你能对着我再说一遍吗？

124
00:11:23,470 --> 00:11:25,610
- Uh, what, to-to Barbara? - Yeah.
- 对着你 对着芭芭拉？ - 对

125
00:11:29,280 --> 00:11:32,550
Um... I'm sorry that I woke you.
对不起 把你吵醒了

126
00:11:34,960 --> 00:11:37,410
Maybe if you'd come home earlier,
要是你能早点回家

127
00:11:37,430 --> 00:11:39,300
we could have spent the evening together.
咱们今晚本该待在一起的

128
00:11:40,470 --> 00:11:42,350
No, I was... I was working, you know?
我 我在加班 你懂的

129
00:11:42,370 --> 00:11:44,110
I came straight home after work.
下班后我就直接回来了

130
00:11:44,120 --> 00:11:45,680
Be honest with me, please.
诚实点吧

131
00:11:46,690 --> 00:11:48,190
I can smell it on your breath.
你身上那酒气我都闻得见

132
00:11:50,940 --> 00:11:52,750
I had a few beers.
我就去喝了一点啤酒

133
00:11:52,770 --> 00:11:54,040
Define a few.
一点是多少？

134
00:11:54,050 --> 00:11:55,520
Well, it was a hard day.
唉 今天太累了

135
00:11:56,470 --> 00:11:57,670
I needed to wind down.
我得喝点放松放松

136
00:11:57,680 --> 00:11:59,720
All you ever do is wind down.
你不成天在放松吗？

137
00:12:00,190 --> 00:12:01,990
You're always at the store.
成天呆在那店里

138
00:12:06,150 --> 00:12:07,560
You want kids, right?
你想要孩子 对吧？

139
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:10,700
- We both do. - Well, you know...
- 咱们都想要 - 但你要知道...

140
00:12:10,710 --> 00:12:12,040
having a family takes money,
养孩子得花钱

141
00:12:12,050 --> 00:12:13,630
which means someone has to work.
总得有人去挣钱

142
00:12:14,360 --> 00:12:15,990
Unless being a professional student
除非现在当学生

143
00:12:16,010 --> 00:12:17,780
is considered a job these days.
也能算份工作了

144
00:12:17,790 --> 00:12:20,100
That's not fair. You know I had to take time off.
你不能这么说 你知道我得休学一段时间

145
00:12:20,120 --> 00:12:21,730
Well, it's not my fault if you can't keep up.
你自己跟不上 凭什么怪我

146
00:12:21,740 --> 00:12:22,940
How are you going to be a lawyer
连法学院都搞不定

147
00:12:22,960 --> 00:12:24,910
if you can't even handle law school?
还想怎么当律师？

148
00:12:26,360 --> 00:12:27,880
Who do you think pays for everything
当你这个三十岁的“大一新生”

149
00:12:27,900 --> 00:12:29,170
while you're gallivanting around campus
在学校里到处瞎逛时

150
00:12:29,180 --> 00:12:30,930
like a 30-year-old freshman?
也不想想谁在供你上学？

151
00:12:31,480 --> 00:12:33,150
I'll give you a hint: it's me.
提示你一下 那就是我

152
00:12:34,050 --> 00:12:36,180
I pay for your school, I pay for your time off school,
你上学是我供 休学也是我供

153
00:12:36,190 --> 00:12:37,670
I pay for the roof over your head.
连住这儿都还是我在供

154
00:12:37,690 --> 00:12:39,130
- Can I talk now? - No! No.
- 我能说句话吗？ - 不 我还没说完

155
00:12:39,150 --> 00:12:41,040
Because I'd like to know, what do you think happens
我倒想知道 要是你真混到毕业了

156
00:12:41,060 --> 00:12:42,380
if you do manage to graduate?
又会发生什么？

157
00:12:42,400 --> 00:12:44,810
You know, you pop out a kid, then leave me with the bill.
生个娃 然后继续把账单甩给我吗？

158
00:12:45,560 --> 00:12:48,030
Or am I stuck at home changing diapers because
还是你天天忙你的第一份工作

159
00:12:48,040 --> 00:12:50,160
you're too busy working for the first time in your life?
让我在家里给娃换屎尿？

160
00:12:50,180 --> 00:12:52,340
- Now you're being cruel. - I'm being honest.
- 你这话太过分了 - 我只是说实话

161
00:12:52,840 --> 00:12:54,720
I thought that's what you always wanted.
在我看来这就是你的追求

162
00:12:56,010 --> 00:12:57,900
Just because you didn't get to be an architect doesn't mean--
你没考上建筑师 并不代表...

163
00:12:57,910 --> 00:12:59,540
I am a fucking architect!
老子就是建筑师！

164
00:13:00,950 --> 00:13:03,850
God damn it, I'm just stuck selling shit furniture because
我之所以得成天在那破店里卖这些玩意儿

165
00:13:03,870 --> 00:13:07,040
someone won't get off their fat fucking ass and help me!
就是因为某个懒猪在家混吃等死 根本不肯出力

166
00:13:15,140 --> 00:13:16,570
How do you feel, Clark?
克拉克 现在感觉怎么样？

167
00:13:21,970 --> 00:13:23,560
Who am I talking to?
我在跟谁说话呢？

168
00:13:23,580 --> 00:13:25,340
- Me, here, now. - You? Okay.
- 和我 此刻 此地 - 哦 你啊 好吧

169
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:27,900
Um...
那个...

170
00:13:29,050 --> 00:13:31,190
I'm sorry, I didn't mean to, uh...
对不起 我不是有意说...

171
00:13:31,300 --> 00:13:33,150
...you know, get angry
就是 刚才发火了

172
00:13:33,170 --> 00:13:35,520
or lose my temper or whatever.
情绪失控了那种

173
00:13:35,900 --> 00:13:36,960
I know.
我知道

174
00:13:37,500 --> 00:13:39,700
That's the purpose of the whole exercise.
练习的目的就在这儿

175
00:13:40,880 --> 00:13:42,250
This is a good start.
这是一个不错的开始

176
00:13:42,770 --> 00:13:44,460
To feel what you feel,
正视你的感受

177
00:13:44,470 --> 00:13:46,630
and then learn to identify a new path.
然后慢慢找出一条新路

178
00:13:48,050 --> 00:13:50,850
Your reaction was actually quite normal.
你的反应其实很正常

179
00:13:53,850 --> 00:13:55,290
Well, that's me!
呵呵 我就这德行

180
00:13:56,230 --> 00:13:59,030
Well, ahoy there, mateys!
哟 伙计们 瞧瞧这儿啊！

181
00:13:59,040 --> 00:14:03,080
Tired of spending your hard-earned doubloons on overpriced furniture?
还打算把金币全砸在那些冤大头家具上？

182
00:14:03,100 --> 00:14:05,990
Looking for deals that'll shiver your timbers?
想买惊掉下巴的跳海价吗？

183
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:09,750
Then come on down to Cap'n Clark's Ottoman Empire,
赶快来克船长的家具帝国！

184
00:14:09,770 --> 00:14:13,580
the Santa Clara Valley's favorite warehouse and showrooms.
圣克拉拉谷的头号家具大卖场

185
00:14:09,770 --> 00:14:13,590
{\an8}【圣克拉拉谷：位于美国西部】

186
00:14:13,590 --> 00:14:15,660
You'll find bedrooms, living rooms,
卧室 客厅 餐厅 书房 浴室

187
00:14:15,680 --> 00:14:18,680
dinettes, dens and bathrooms aplenty.
全屋家具 应有尽有！

188
00:14:18,690 --> 00:14:21,210
First-time homeowners? We've got ya.
刚买房的？来这儿就对了！

189
00:14:21,230 --> 00:14:23,620
New parents looking for Billy's first crib?
新当爹妈的？

190
00:14:23,630 --> 00:14:24,880
We've got ya!
来这就对了！

191
00:14:24,890 --> 00:14:26,830
From the latest in modern design
时髦现代样样全

192
00:14:26,850 --> 00:14:28,970
to the classic styles of yesteryear,
经典复古通通有

193
00:14:28,980 --> 00:14:31,440
it's all here and it's all a steal.
价格低到没对手

194
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:33,300
What's that, Polly?
怎么啦 波莉？

195
00:14:33,320 --> 00:14:34,890
You're worried about credit?
信用卡里钱不够？

196
00:14:34,910 --> 00:14:38,910
Ha! Cap'n Clark says no credit, no problem!
哈哈！在克船长这儿 钱不够 没问题！

197
00:14:38,920 --> 00:14:41,010
Sail the high seas of high quality,
快来畅游顶级家具海洋

198
00:14:41,020 --> 00:14:43,660
and leave your money problems at the door.
把钱的问题统统抛在脑后

199
00:14:43,670 --> 00:14:44,830
Walk in today
今天就来店里

200
00:14:44,840 --> 00:14:46,870
and get your dream sectional lounger,
把梦想直接搬回家！

201
00:14:46,890 --> 00:14:49,890
kitchen table, floor lamp, and bed frame here
桌椅板凳 灯具摆件随便挑！

202
00:14:49,900 --> 00:14:52,670
at Cap'n Clark's Ottoman Empire,
克船长的家具帝国

203
00:14:52,690 --> 00:14:55,490
located at Capitol and McKee, just off the 680.
就在680号公路出口 国会路和麦基路口

204
00:14:56,200 --> 00:14:57,840
Arr! Walk in today...
嘿吼！赶紧过来...

205
00:14:58,980 --> 00:15:00,310
...kick your feet back,
翘起二郎腿

206
00:15:00,330 --> 00:15:02,780
and enjoy an empire of your own!
当你的家具大王！

207
00:15:02,790 --> 00:15:05,200
For every sultan deserves a throne,
毕竟 国王得有王座

208
00:15:05,210 --> 00:15:07,200
and we've got one with your name on it,
而你的专属王座 就在这儿等着你

209
00:15:07,210 --> 00:15:08,970
here at Cap'n Clark's--
就在克船长的...

210
00:15:09,800 --> 00:15:10,700
No way!
卧槽

211
00:15:11,300 --> 00:15:13,140
- Clark, you good? - Turn the camera off.
- 克拉克 没事吧？ - 快把相机关了

212
00:15:13,150 --> 00:15:14,860
No, no, it's good. It's outtake stuff, dude.
不不 拍得好 这种花絮才有趣

213
00:15:14,880 --> 00:15:17,260
- Turn the fucking camera off. - Okay... Jesus...
- 赶紧给老子关掉 - 好吧...我的天

214
00:15:19,520 --> 00:15:21,010
You, uh, you need help?
那个 要帮忙吗？

215
00:15:21,030 --> 00:15:22,760
No, I got it, I got it.
不用 我自己来

216
00:15:23,890 --> 00:15:25,010
Um...
那个...

217
00:15:25,030 --> 00:15:27,390
- Are we going again, or...? - No.
- 还要重拍吗？ - 不拍了

218
00:15:27,400 --> 00:15:29,270
Kat, you can open the store now.
小凯 去开门营业吧

219
00:15:29,590 --> 00:15:31,330
We've been open.
早就开了

220
00:15:30,730 --> 00:15:34,200
{\an8}（全店促销 低价保证 一件不留 全场甩卖）

221
00:15:33,370 --> 00:15:35,640
You know, dude, I still don't get it.
老哥 我还是没搞懂

222
00:15:34,270 --> 00:15:38,590
{\an8}（结束南非种族隔离）

223
00:15:35,660 --> 00:15:38,570
Are you, like, a pirate or a sultan?
你演的是海盗还是国王？

224
00:15:38,590 --> 00:15:40,930
- Just be good to establish it. - I'm a... Shut up.
- 最好还是明确一下 - 我是个...闭嘴

225
00:15:40,950 --> 00:15:41,790
{\an8}（结束南非种族隔离）

226
00:15:41,800 --> 00:15:44,770
Piece of cheap particleboard bullshit.
刨花板做的破椅子

227
00:15:45,210 --> 00:15:46,740
Clear this stuff up, will you?
快把这东西弄走 听到没？

228
00:15:47,670 --> 00:15:48,840
Here.
拿着

229
00:15:49,790 --> 00:15:52,820
{\an8}（全店促销 低价保证 一件不留 全场甩卖）

230
00:15:59,110 --> 00:16:04,220
{\an8}（1990年6月）

231
00:16:05,400 --> 00:16:06,400
Shit.
该死

232
00:16:06,890 --> 00:16:07,820
Sorry about that.
抱歉

233
00:16:08,690 --> 00:16:10,030
How's it looking?
怎么样 查出来没？

234
00:16:10,050 --> 00:16:11,610
Meter reads fine.
电表没问题

235
00:16:11,630 --> 00:16:14,100
If your bill's coming in high, that's on you.
电费要是高 只能是你自己用得多

236
00:16:14,770 --> 00:16:17,300
What about the outages? That happens after hours.
那跳电的事怎么说 打烊后就出现

237
00:16:17,880 --> 00:16:21,080
Don't know. Fluorescents must be tripping a breaker.
没准是荧光灯出问题 导致跳闸了

238
00:16:22,180 --> 00:16:25,600
I turn the overheads off when the store closes,
但是一打烊我就把顶灯都关了

239
00:16:25,610 --> 00:16:26,910
before the power gets weird.
还没闪之前就关了

240
00:16:27,730 --> 00:16:29,770
Anyway, wouldn't that just make the bills go down?
而且如果真是那样 电费不该更少吗？

241
00:16:32,920 --> 00:16:34,430
Where's your breaker box?
配电箱在哪儿？

242
00:16:36,050 --> 00:16:37,000
I'm no expert,
虽然我不是专家

243
00:16:37,010 --> 00:16:39,990
but I checked earlier, and everything looks okay.
但我之前看过了 没看出什么问题

244
00:16:40,010 --> 00:16:42,500
- You said the lights flicker. - Yeah, the whole store does.
- 你说灯会闪 - 对 整个店都闪

245
00:16:42,510 --> 00:16:43,920
- Huh. - Just not at the same time.
- 是吗？ - 只是不一起闪

246
00:16:43,930 --> 00:16:45,240
One night, I lose the power upstairs.
有一晚是楼上

247
00:16:45,250 --> 00:16:48,190
Next night, it's down here. There's no rhyme or...
下一晚就变成了楼下 完全没规律

248
00:16:55,530 --> 00:16:56,960
Who the hell installed this thing?
谁装的这鬼东西？

249
00:16:57,710 --> 00:16:59,730
Well, the building came wired.
这房子买来时 回路就这样接的

250
00:17:00,130 --> 00:17:02,110
I mean, it's dated, but it's not that old.
虽然有点年头 但也不至于不能用

251
00:17:08,360 --> 00:17:09,420
Take a look at this.
你来看看这个

252
00:17:14,160 --> 00:17:15,260
That wasn't there before.
之前没这东西

253
00:17:16,050 --> 00:17:17,050
Or...
也许...

254
00:17:17,970 --> 00:17:20,420
maybe I didn't notice. Like I say, I'm no expert.
是我没注意到 我不是专家

255
00:17:20,430 --> 00:17:23,170
Why-why is it... why is it going that way?
为...为什么是斜着的？

256
00:17:23,380 --> 00:17:25,090
Better question:
应该问的是

257
00:17:25,660 --> 00:17:27,360
what is it even connected to?
这东西到底连到哪儿了

258
00:17:28,830 --> 00:17:30,030
Huh?
懂吗？

259
00:17:37,220 --> 00:17:39,490
Kat! How's the power?
小凯 楼上灯怎么样？

260
00:17:40,510 --> 00:17:41,530
What?
干嘛？

261
00:17:41,540 --> 00:17:43,380
Anything happen up there?
上面有反应吗？

262
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:44,600
What the hell?
怎么搞的

263
00:17:45,210 --> 00:17:46,550
The rat's back.
老鼠又来了

264
00:17:46,820 --> 00:17:48,720
- But the power's on. - Yeah.
- 灯还正常吧 - 正常

265
00:17:48,730 --> 00:17:50,220
I thought we killed the rat.
我还以为咱们已经把老鼠给干掉了

266
00:17:50,240 --> 00:17:51,560
We killed  "a"  rat.
咱们才干掉了一只

267
00:17:53,140 --> 00:17:55,630
- So is this the problem? - Don't see how.
- 这就是问题原因吗？ - 没道理啊

268
00:17:55,650 --> 00:17:57,510
Power can't even go through this part of the circuit.
电路根本不走这里

269
00:17:58,220 --> 00:17:59,420
It's just...
它纯粹是...

270
00:17:59,730 --> 00:18:01,000
there.
莫名其妙出现在这

271
00:18:01,140 --> 00:18:04,500
Like some schmo just stuck it in there.
像被哪个笨蛋随便塞进去的

272
00:18:05,480 --> 00:18:06,740
Yeah.
没错

273
00:18:14,650 --> 00:18:17,780
Do you ever feel like you're living behind glass?
你是否觉得生活像被隔在了一层玻璃之后？

274
00:18:17,790 --> 00:18:19,610
Watching life happen,
看着世界在眼前上演

275
00:18:19,630 --> 00:18:21,900
but never really stepping into it?
自己却只能旁观？

276
00:18:22,990 --> 00:18:26,490
Maybe it's time to open the window within.
现在 是时候打开心灵之窗了

277
00:18:27,130 --> 00:18:29,640
You can be the author of your own design
你可以重新定义自己的人生

278
00:18:29,660 --> 00:18:31,640
because we all deserve another chance
我们每个人 都值得拥有另一次机会

279
00:18:31,650 --> 00:18:33,560
to fulfill our dreams.
让梦想重新启航

280
00:18:33,640 --> 00:18:36,120
The moment you believe change is possible,
只要你相信改变是可能的

281
00:18:36,130 --> 00:18:37,910
you've already begun.
你就已经开始了这段旅程

282
00:18:37,920 --> 00:18:39,580
Order The Window Within
立即订购《心灵之窗》

283
00:18:38,880 --> 00:18:39,580
{\an8}(《心灵之窗》)

284
00:18:39,600 --> 00:18:42,180
and the companion three-part audio program,
以及配套的三辑音频课程

285
00:18:39,600 --> 00:18:42,190
{\an8}（突破障碍 掌控人生
打破那扇窗）

286
00:18:42,190 --> 00:18:45,490
Guided Openings, by Dr. Mary Klein.
《引导之门》 均由玛丽·克莱因医生倾力呈现

287
00:18:43,780 --> 00:18:47,870
{\an8}（三辑音频课程）

288
00:18:45,510 --> 00:18:48,100
Available now for $24.95 plus shipping.
现价24.95美元 运费另计

289
00:18:48,920 --> 00:18:53,290
Call 1-800-555-0199.
请拨打1-800-555-0199

290
00:18:54,350 --> 00:18:55,220
{\an8}（克里斯·弗格森公司出品）

291
00:18:54,760 --> 00:18:57,320
It's never too late to forge a new path.
开辟一条新路 永远不晚

292
00:18:55,240 --> 00:18:58,430
{\an8}【克里斯·弗格森：《后室》电影制片人】

293
00:18:59,350 --> 00:19:01,720
"So, you're still trusting paper folders,
“你居然还在信任纸质文件夹”

294
00:19:01,740 --> 00:19:04,050
"mislabeled tapes, and a locked filing cabinet
“贴错标签的磁带 还有个谁拿把钥匙”

295
00:19:04,070 --> 00:19:06,000
"that anyone with a spare key can open?"
“都能开的文件柜？”

296
00:19:06,010 --> 00:19:08,250
"Your business runs on information,
“信息决定企业的生死”

297
00:19:08,260 --> 00:19:10,860
"yet most companies treat their data like clutter..."
“但大多数公司却把数据当成了堆杂物...”

298
00:19:14,920 --> 00:19:17,060
That small blip is not an asteroid.
那个信号不是小行星

299
00:19:17,070 --> 00:19:18,950
It's a spaceship, and it's on our tail.
是一艘飞船 它咬住我们了

300
00:19:18,620 --> 00:19:23,766
{\an8}（1970年圣克鲁斯现代主义建筑设计论坛）

301
00:19:18,970 --> 00:19:21,270
- It's getting closer. - Impossible, Rigna.
- 它在靠近 - 不可能 里格娜

302
00:19:21,290 --> 00:19:23,810
They couldn't have spotted us. We have our radar shield on.
他们不可能发现我们 雷达隐身还开着呢

303
00:19:23,830 --> 00:19:26,370
I know that, sir, but they are gaining on us.
我知道 长官 但他们追上来了

304
00:19:26,700 --> 00:19:28,960
Is it possible Earth has a secret device
难道地球人有某种秘密设备

305
00:19:28,980 --> 00:19:30,520
that can penetrate our radar shield?
能穿透我们的雷达隐身罩？

306
00:20:06,430 --> 00:20:08,070
Piece of shit.
垃圾

307
00:20:55,270 --> 00:20:58,070
"Why did you do this to yourself?"
“为什么 你要这样对待自己？”

308
00:21:02,030 --> 00:21:03,390
"How did you get here?"
“你是怎么来到这里的？”

309
00:21:06,940 --> 00:21:10,860
"Your consciousness is a room full of memories
“你的意识 就像一个装满记忆的房间”

310
00:21:10,880 --> 00:21:13,350
"that is constantly evolving."
“它在时刻重构 在无限演变”

311
00:21:12,640 --> 00:21:15,070
{\an8}（收音机 磁带）

312
00:21:15,550 --> 00:21:17,160
"But as you walk through life,
“在普通人的生活中”

313
00:21:17,930 --> 00:21:20,720
"the untrained mind can start to build walls,
“不自知的人会开始筑墙”

314
00:21:22,190 --> 00:21:23,700
"put up barriers
“建立屏障”

315
00:21:24,750 --> 00:21:27,160
"to protect itself from the outside world."
“隔绝外界”

316
00:21:28,540 --> 00:21:30,500
"It's a natural response."
“这是本能反应”

317
00:21:31,520 --> 00:21:33,830
"Something we are often unaware of."
“我们常常对此毫无察觉”

318
00:21:34,750 --> 00:21:36,720
"But if gone unchecked,
“但久而久之”

319
00:21:36,730 --> 00:21:38,640
"it can leave you feeling trapped."
“你会发现 自己被囚禁了”

320
00:21:40,350 --> 00:21:42,660
"You can become convinced that the world outside
“你会说服自己”

321
00:21:42,670 --> 00:21:44,730
"is better off without you."
“外面的世界不需要你”

322
00:21:45,130 --> 00:21:47,720
"That you never deserve the relationships you've had."
“你会告诉自己 自己不配被爱”

323
00:21:48,610 --> 00:21:51,240
"Resigned to watch your life unfold
“于是 你只能蜷缩在窗后”

324
00:21:51,250 --> 00:21:53,350
"from behind a lone window."
“当个旁观者 静静地看着生活上演”

325
00:21:55,450 --> 00:21:57,790
"I can help you open it now
“让我来帮你打开”

326
00:21:58,910 --> 00:22:00,910
"because the window isn't locked."
“因为窗户根本没锁”

327
00:22:02,830 --> 00:22:04,890
"The latch was never broken."
“门也没有封死”

328
00:22:08,180 --> 00:22:09,980
"Are you ready to step through?"
“准备好跨过去了吗？”

329
00:22:12,740 --> 00:22:15,810
"So that you can reclaim that which was once yours...
“去夺回属于你的东西”

330
00:22:17,510 --> 00:22:20,470
"and take back control of your life."
“去重新主宰你的生命”

331
00:22:22,350 --> 00:22:24,220
"The life you want to be living."
“去过你想过的人生”

332
00:22:25,820 --> 00:22:28,370
"Unburdened by the traumas of the past."
“卸下过去的重负”

333
00:22:29,450 --> 00:22:32,170
"Free of the confines you had built."
“走出那些你亲手打造的围墙”

334
00:22:32,180 --> 00:22:33,780
...to leave, and so I decided...
...所以我想...

335
00:22:33,810 --> 00:22:37,330
"And free to choose a path of your own design."
“开辟一条属于你自己的路”

336
00:23:06,960 --> 00:23:10,490
{\an8}（家庭牙科诊所 米莱服饰）

337
00:23:10,500 --> 00:23:13,560
{\an8}（停）

338
00:23:14,130 --> 00:23:16,440
"Well, hey there, cowboys and cowgirls!"
“嘿 牛仔们 快瞧这边！”

339
00:23:16,460 --> 00:23:18,110
"Are you looking to rustle up the best deals
“想在格兰德河这块地盘”

340
00:23:16,460 --> 00:23:19,660
{\an8}【格兰德河：位于美国南部】

341
00:23:18,120 --> 00:23:19,460
"this side of the Rio Grande?"
“抢到最便宜的家具吗？”

342
00:23:19,670 --> 00:23:20,300
Prick.
混球

343
00:23:20,310 --> 00:23:23,400
"Well, yeehaw, I say yeehaw!"
“咿吼！快来大韦恩家具店！”

344
00:23:23,420 --> 00:23:25,240
"Here at Big Wayne's, our dining room sets
“买了我们的餐厅套装”

345
00:23:25,260 --> 00:23:27,760
"are gonna make you feel like you just struck gold."
“就跟挖到金矿一样！”

346
00:23:27,770 --> 00:23:30,360
"So don't even think about going anyplace else."
“别去管那些破店”

347
00:23:30,370 --> 00:23:32,680
"Big Wayne's, just look for the golden--"
“认准大韦恩 认准金色招...”

348
00:23:30,370 --> 00:23:32,680
{\an8}（大韦恩家具店）

349
00:23:48,490 --> 00:23:49,760
What the...
搞什么...

350
00:23:57,030 --> 00:23:57,770
{\an8}（由此下楼）

351
00:23:59,810 --> 00:24:01,140
{\an8}（由此下楼）

352
00:24:06,570 --> 00:24:07,390
Stupid...
该死

353
00:24:07,400 --> 00:24:09,770
Fuck! Piece of shit!
看老子怎么修理你

354
00:29:04,380 --> 00:29:06,800
{\an8}（亭亻）

355
00:29:48,690 --> 00:29:52,780
（粤语）“各位好吗？祝各位平安健康快乐”

356
00:29:53,270 --> 00:29:55,690
（阿卡德语）“愿一切都很好”

357
00:29:56,670 --> 00:29:59,300
（俄语）“你好 欢迎你们”

358
00:29:59,700 --> 00:30:02,550
（泰语）“远方土地的朋友们 你们好”

359
00:30:02,570 --> 00:30:06,290
（泰语）“在这片土地上的我们 向你们所有人致以诚挚的问候”

360
00:30:06,640 --> 00:30:09,760
（阿拉伯语）“我们向星际中的朋友们致以问候”

361
00:30:09,940 --> 00:30:12,730
（阿拉伯语）“但愿时间能让我们相聚”

362
00:30:12,740 --> 00:30:15,010
（罗马尼亚语）“向大家问好”

363
00:30:16,140 --> 00:30:17,980
（法语）“大家好”

