I learned to push people away before they could hurt me.
我学会了在被伤害之前 抢先一步把别人推开

913
01:15:15,240 --> 01:15:18,270
And, now, as an adult,
而现在 我成年了

914
01:15:18,950 --> 01:15:23,100
I'm still stuck right where I started.
我依然留在原地

915
01:15:26,050 --> 01:15:27,550
Alone.
唯我一人

916
01:15:29,530 --> 01:15:30,760
What is this?
怎么回事？

917
01:15:33,000 --> 01:15:35,760
It's a real mess. Am I right?
真是一团糟 对吧？

918
01:15:35,900 --> 01:15:37,300
Clark...
克拉克...

919
01:15:38,570 --> 01:15:39,740
...let me help you...
让我来帮你...

920
01:15:41,930 --> 01:15:43,760
before you do anything you can't take back.
在你做出无法挽回的事之前

921
01:15:43,780 --> 01:15:45,240
Answer the question.
回答我的问题

922
01:15:46,430 --> 01:15:49,020
Yes, it's a real mess.
是的 真是一团糟

923
01:15:51,690 --> 01:15:54,580
But also beautiful in a way.
但从某种角度看 也很美

924
01:15:55,060 --> 01:15:56,040
No?
不是吗？

925
01:16:03,760 --> 01:16:04,960
Who are these people?
这些人是谁？

926
01:16:07,170 --> 01:16:08,770
This place builds them.
这地方造了他们

927
01:16:09,280 --> 01:16:12,770
Oh, actually, more like it remembers them.
哦 其实更像是在记得他们

928
01:16:14,250 --> 01:16:16,680
And the more times it remembers something,
只不过记得越多

929
01:16:16,690 --> 01:16:18,180
the less it does.
就越走样

930
01:16:19,410 --> 01:16:23,110
Somewhere out there is a guy in a striped shirt,
这个在外面是个穿条纹衫的家伙

931
01:16:23,120 --> 01:16:25,030
but, in here, he's...
但在这儿...

932
01:16:26,980 --> 01:16:28,210
remembered.
他被记成了这样

933
01:16:28,950 --> 01:16:31,460
Just slightly wrong.
有点走样

934
01:16:32,680 --> 01:16:34,540
Somewhere out there is a man
这个在外面是个...

935
01:16:34,560 --> 01:16:36,990
in a wheelchair, and a lamp.
坐轮椅的家伙 带了盏灯

936
01:16:46,040 --> 01:16:48,220
I'm pretty sure that's how you get all of this.
我敢说 这里就是这么回事

937
01:16:48,480 --> 01:16:50,380
You know, all these places
所有这些地方啊

938
01:16:50,570 --> 01:16:53,410
and rooms and buildings
房间和建筑啊

939
01:16:54,310 --> 01:16:55,870
misremembering themselves.
全都记岔了

940
01:16:56,020 --> 01:16:57,350
Clark...
克拉克...

941
01:16:57,720 --> 01:16:59,120
let's talk this through.
我们好好谈谈吧

942
01:17:00,260 --> 01:17:01,560
In some ways...
换个角度看...

943
01:17:02,330 --> 01:17:04,840
they're an improvement on the originals.
他们甚至比原件更好

944
01:17:06,980 --> 01:17:08,350
For starters,
比如...

945
01:17:09,250 --> 01:17:10,780
they can't feel anything.
他们没有任何感觉

946
01:17:21,850 --> 01:17:23,780
Can you imagine how good that must feel?
想象一下 那样得有多自在啊

947
01:17:26,570 --> 01:17:27,860
I mean...
我是说...

948
01:17:28,550 --> 01:17:32,050
...there's no thoughts or pain, no ego...
没念头 没痛苦 没自我...

949
01:17:33,580 --> 01:17:34,800
...no fear.
也没恐惧

950
01:17:36,040 --> 01:17:37,580
They simply...
纯粹就是...

951
01:17:38,610 --> 01:17:39,950
exist.
在那儿

952
01:17:40,970 --> 01:17:43,570
Like... like furniture!
就像...就像家具一样

953
01:17:46,620 --> 01:17:49,060
Look at this. The best part.
看这儿 最绝的来了

954
01:17:53,350 --> 01:17:54,460
You can eat them!
他们能吃

955
01:18:36,680 --> 01:18:38,180
That's my, uh...
这是我的 呃...

956
01:18:38,210 --> 01:18:39,840
assistant manager.
助理

957
01:18:42,360 --> 01:18:44,270
I tried to help her, but she just, uh...
我想帮她 但她就是...

958
01:18:45,070 --> 01:18:46,340
Clark!
克拉克

959
01:18:47,380 --> 01:18:50,550
If you untie me, we can talk this through,
你把我解开 我们可以聊聊

960
01:18:50,860 --> 01:18:52,080
get you feeling better.
让你心里好受点

961
01:18:52,090 --> 01:18:53,840
Yeah, well, what if I did untie you?
是吗 就算解开了

962
01:18:53,850 --> 01:18:55,320
You know, what then?
那又怎样？

963
01:18:55,650 --> 01:18:57,040
You'd run around here
你顶多像个

964
01:18:57,050 --> 01:18:58,550
like a chicken with its head cut off,
没头苍蝇一样到处乱窜

965
01:18:58,570 --> 01:18:59,820
looking for a way out.
找你的出口

966
01:19:00,770 --> 01:19:03,250
But you'd end up in the same place you are now.
但你最后还是得回到这儿

967
01:19:04,530 --> 01:19:07,030
Like the path thing you're always talking about.
就跟你爱说的那套路径理论一样

968
01:19:07,830 --> 01:19:09,160
Clark!
克拉克

969
01:19:09,610 --> 01:19:12,150
I just want to help you. Just tell me what you need.
我是真的想帮你 只要告诉我你想要什么

970
01:19:13,150 --> 01:19:14,780
I'll-I'll-I'll do it.
我...我...我一定照做

971
01:19:16,670 --> 01:19:17,380
Yeah?
是吗？

972
01:19:17,400 --> 01:19:19,400
Yeah. Yes, please.
是的 是的 拜托了

973
01:19:22,500 --> 01:19:23,500
Okay.
行

974
01:19:25,770 --> 01:19:27,160
Well, I want you to tell me
我想听你亲口说

975
01:19:27,180 --> 01:19:28,850
that I didn't do anything wrong, you know,
我没做错任何事

976
01:19:28,860 --> 01:19:30,640
that-that you were wrong about me.
是你之前对我看走眼了

977
01:19:30,660 --> 01:19:33,300
I was wrong about you! I was.
是我看走眼了 是我错了

978
01:19:33,320 --> 01:19:35,730
- I was wrong about you. - No, no, not-not like that.
- 我真的看错你了 - 不 不 不要这样

979
01:19:36,980 --> 01:19:38,840
Not... not so fast, okay?
别 别这么快 好吗？

980
01:19:40,250 --> 01:19:42,320
I mean, I wanna... I want to set the scene first!
我的意思是 我想...我想先定个场景

981
01:19:46,400 --> 01:19:48,740
Let's start, um...
咱们从...

982
01:19:49,550 --> 01:19:51,020
well, the night that, uh...
嗯...从那晚开始

983
01:19:51,810 --> 01:19:54,820
that I got kicked out of my own house.
就是我被撵出我自己家的那晚

984
01:19:54,940 --> 01:19:55,680
Yeah?
怎么样？

985
01:19:58,620 --> 01:20:00,420
It was, um... It was late.
那天 嗯...很晚了

986
01:20:01,840 --> 01:20:03,410
A lot darker.
屋里很暗

987
01:20:04,240 --> 01:20:05,050
Uh...
呃...

988
01:20:07,720 --> 01:20:08,810
Lights, please.
关下灯

989
01:20:19,330 --> 01:20:20,550
I tried this exercise with her before.
之前跟她试过

990
01:20:20,560 --> 01:20:22,780
It doesn't go anywhere.
她根本不会动 结果都一样

991
01:20:24,210 --> 01:20:25,260
Fine!
行

992
01:20:25,740 --> 01:20:27,260
I'll do it myself.
我自己来

993
01:20:27,970 --> 01:20:29,810
It's still my house after all.
毕竟 这终究还是我的房子

994
01:20:33,470 --> 01:20:34,600
Yeah.
好了

995
01:20:36,340 --> 01:20:37,850
Thank you. Much better.
谢谢 这样才对

996
01:20:39,660 --> 01:20:40,860
But there's...
不过...

997
01:20:41,780 --> 01:20:42,630
still...
还是...

998
01:20:43,940 --> 01:20:45,320
something off.
缺点儿什么

999
01:21:03,240 --> 01:21:04,840
Clark, please...
克拉克 求你..

1000
01:21:36,860 --> 01:21:39,390
No, please, don't, don't...!
不 拜托 不要 不要...

1001
01:21:57,890 --> 01:21:58,930
I'm sorry.
对不起

1002
01:22:02,110 --> 01:22:03,050
I'm sorry, I...
对不起 我...

1003
01:22:04,590 --> 01:22:07,790
broke the glass and woke you up.
把杯子打碎了 还把你吵醒了

1004
01:22:10,230 --> 01:22:12,240
I know how you like to sleep early.
我知道你睡得早

1005
01:22:16,530 --> 01:22:18,370
I was at the store late.
我在店里忙太久了

1006
01:22:20,190 --> 01:22:22,270
I guess I lost track of the time.
就忘了时间

1007
01:22:25,060 --> 01:22:26,720
I was checking inventory.
我之前在对账

1008
01:22:27,280 --> 01:22:28,160
But...
然后...

1009
01:22:28,900 --> 01:22:30,980
I stopped off for a few beers.
顺路去喝了一点啤酒

1010
01:22:30,990 --> 01:22:32,530
- Clark-- - Barbara!
- 克拉克 - 芭芭拉

1011
01:22:34,280 --> 01:22:36,250
I was checking inventory.
我之前在对账

1012
01:22:38,110 --> 01:22:40,250
Then I stopped off for a few beers.
然后顺路去喝了一点啤酒

1013
01:22:45,160 --> 01:22:47,130
Defi-define a few.
一点...一点是多少？

1014
01:22:47,150 --> 01:22:48,650
As many as I wanted.
我想喝多少就喝多少

1015
01:22:50,070 --> 01:22:51,440
Because this is my house.
因为这房子是我的

1016
01:22:53,110 --> 01:22:54,480
I pay for it.
房贷都是我在还

1017
01:22:55,670 --> 01:22:58,350
I pay for everything. I pay for you to go to school.
所有的钱都是我在出 你上学是我供

1018
01:22:59,530 --> 01:23:01,170
I pay for your time off school!
休学也是我供

1019
01:23:01,930 --> 01:23:03,860
I pay for the roof over your head!
连住这儿都是我在供

1020
01:23:05,600 --> 01:23:07,000
You want kids, right?
你想要孩子 对吧？

1021
01:23:07,720 --> 01:23:08,970
Well, that takes money.
养孩子得花钱

1022
01:23:08,990 --> 01:23:10,480
So someone has to work around here.
总得有人去挣钱

1023
01:23:12,760 --> 01:23:13,970
I said someone has
我说过了这儿得有人干活

1024
01:23:13,970 --> 01:23:15,970
to get off her fat ass and work around here!
不能在那儿当个懒猪混吃等死

1025
01:23:16,720 --> 01:23:18,930
Just because you didn't get to be an architect don--
你没考上建筑师 并不代表...

1026
01:23:18,940 --> 01:23:20,670
I am a fucking architect.
老子就是建筑师

1027
01:23:22,110 --> 01:23:24,600
I'm just stuck selling shit furniture because someone
我之所以得成天在那破店里卖这些玩意儿

1028
01:23:24,610 --> 01:23:27,360
won't get off her fat fucking ass and help me!
就是因为某个懒猪在家混吃等死 根本不肯出力！

1029
01:23:27,370 --> 01:23:29,430
- I'm not your wife! - Stay in character.
- 我才不是你老婆 - 别出戏

1030
01:23:30,480 --> 01:23:31,350
Stay in character!
继续演

1031
01:23:31,370 --> 01:23:33,580
- I've never even met her! - STAY IN CHARACTER!
- 我压根就没见过她 - 继续演你的角色

1032
01:23:33,590 --> 01:23:35,290
FUCK YOU!
滚你妈的蛋！

1033
01:23:38,210 --> 01:23:39,020
What did you say?
你说什么？

1034
01:23:39,030 --> 01:23:41,840
You wanna know the real reason your wife left you?
你想知道为什么你老婆甩了你吗？

1035
01:23:41,850 --> 01:23:43,490
It wasn't the drinking,
根本不是因为酗酒

1036
01:23:43,500 --> 01:23:47,110
or the stumbling home at all hours, or the rage.
不是半夜烂醉回家 甚至不是你的坏脾气

1037
01:23:47,120 --> 01:23:49,040
It was the whining!
是因为你是个巨婴

1038
01:23:49,050 --> 01:23:51,230
Nothing's ever your fault, is it?
你这辈子没一件事是你的错 对吧？

1039
01:23:51,400 --> 01:23:53,460
You drink too much? Blame your job.
喝多了 赖工作

1040
01:23:53,660 --> 01:23:56,380
You hate your job? Blame the world.
恨职业 赖世界

1041
01:23:56,440 --> 01:23:57,880
You get kicked out of the house?
被撵出家门

1042
01:23:57,900 --> 01:23:59,680
Blame your wife.
赖老婆

1043
01:23:59,700 --> 01:24:01,720
You attack me and tie me up?
现在你攻击我 绑架我

1044
01:24:02,060 --> 01:24:03,280
Blame your brain!
居然还敢赖在脑子上

1045
01:24:03,290 --> 01:24:05,920
You are your fucking brain, you dipshit!
你这颗烂脑子 就是你本人 废物

1046
01:24:10,400 --> 01:24:12,700
- You're saying it's my fault? - Yes!
- 所以 全都是我的错？ - 是啊

1047
01:24:12,720 --> 01:24:15,040
But it's just the way you're wired, isn't it?
但你肯定又要赖你的脑回路 对吧？

1048
01:24:15,050 --> 01:24:16,320
ISN'T IT?!
对不对！

1049
01:24:24,830 --> 01:24:26,560
How do I stop doing that?
那我怎么才能停下来？

1050
01:24:27,470 --> 01:24:30,070
Honestly, I have no fucking idea.
实话实说 我一丁点的招都没有了

1051
01:24:32,730 --> 01:24:34,170
I can't help you, Clark.
我帮不了你 克拉克

1052
01:24:35,030 --> 01:24:36,700
As much as I tried.
能试的我都试了

1053
01:24:38,470 --> 01:24:39,920
It's just not up to me.
这根本不是我能左右的

1054
01:24:43,490 --> 01:24:44,850
I can't save anyone.
我谁也救不了

1055
01:24:54,840 --> 01:24:56,030
You know...
你知道吗？

1056
01:24:58,830 --> 01:25:00,570
I don't think I want to change.
我其实不想改

1057
01:25:03,580 --> 01:25:04,820
Then don't.
那就别改

1058
01:25:11,980 --> 01:25:13,590
I like it in here.
我喜欢这里

1059
01:25:18,040 --> 01:25:19,770
For the first time in a long time,
这么久以来

1060
01:25:19,790 --> 01:25:21,310
I feel like I'm...
我第一次觉得...

1061
01:25:24,800 --> 01:25:27,950
like I'm right where I'm supposed to be.
我终于找到了我的归宿

1062
01:25:30,680 --> 01:25:32,130
Then stay.
那就留下吧

1063
01:25:34,140 --> 01:25:35,140
Right where you are.
就这么待着

1064
01:25:39,990 --> 01:25:41,000
But let me go.
但你得放我走

1065
01:26:10,820 --> 01:26:12,020
I'm sorry.
对不起

1066
01:26:15,900 --> 01:26:17,000
About what?
对不起什么？

1067
01:26:48,030 --> 01:26:49,630
What are you doing in here?
你来这儿干什么？

1068
01:26:56,020 --> 01:26:57,720
This is Mary.
这是玛丽

1069
01:26:58,990 --> 01:27:00,800
She's our therapist.
她是咱们的心理治疗师

1070
01:27:02,340 --> 01:27:03,710
She was just leaving.
她正要离开

1071
01:27:06,000 --> 01:27:07,390
No, no.
不 不

1072
01:27:08,110 --> 01:27:09,650
You don't have to worry.
你不用担心

1073
01:27:11,510 --> 01:27:13,550
She says we don't need to change.
她说咱们不需要改变

1074
01:27:25,930 --> 01:27:27,030
It's okay.
没关系的

1075
01:27:28,820 --> 01:27:30,890
It's just the way we're wired.
咱们的脑回路就是这样接的

1076
01:31:18,960 --> 01:31:21,230
{\an8}（由此下楼）

1077
01:31:24,480 --> 01:31:26,940
（干达语）“向宇宙所有族群致意”

1078
01:31:26,950 --> 01:31:29,040
（干达语）“愿和平永远伴随你们”

1079
01:31:29,060 --> 01:31:37,510
（马拉地语）“地球人民向你们传递美好的祝愿”

1080
01:31:31,700 --> 01:31:34,040
{\an8}（一件不留 全场甩卖）

1081
01:31:37,730 --> 01:31:41,580
（台语）“太空的朋友们 你们好”

1082
01:31:39,000 --> 01:31:41,480
{\an8}（一件不留 全场甩卖）

1083
01:31:41,590 --> 01:31:45,280
（台语）“吃过饭没？来我们这儿坐坐”

1084
01:31:46,920 --> 01:31:48,080
No...
不

1085
01:31:49,630 --> 01:31:51,360
{\an8}（出口）

1086
01:31:55,570 --> 01:31:58,690
（捷克语）“亲爱的朋友们 祝你们万事如意”

1087
01:31:58,870 --> 01:32:02,450
（卡纳达语）“代表说卡纳达语的人们 向你们致以美好祝愿”

1088
01:32:02,560 --> 01:32:06,920
（拉贾斯坦语）“大家好 我们这里很幸福”

1089
01:32:06,930 --> 01:32:09,130
（拉贾斯坦语）“愿你们那里也同样幸福”

1090
01:32:09,140 --> 01:32:12,220
"Hello from the children of planet Earth."
（英语）“来自地球儿童的问候”

1091
01:32:17,180 --> 01:32:24,160
（古希腊语）“你们好 无论你们是谁 我们带着友谊 拜访朋友”

1092
01:32:24,290 --> 01:32:27,260
（葡萄牙语）“愿所有人平安幸福”

1093
01:32:32,650 --> 01:32:35,070
（阿卡德语）“愿一切都很好”

1094
01:32:36,050 --> 01:32:38,680
（俄语）“你好 欢迎你们”

1095
01:32:39,090 --> 01:32:41,940
（泰语）“远方土地的朋友们 你们好...”

1096
01:32:56,320 --> 01:32:58,160
（法语）“大家好”

1097
01:35:16,210 --> 01:35:17,790
Are you okay? Are you okay?
你没事吧？没事吧？

1098
01:35:17,800 --> 01:35:18,900
Who the fuck is that?
这女人是谁？

1099
01:35:18,920 --> 01:35:20,220
Who is it?
你是谁？

1100
01:35:21,960 --> 01:35:23,700
What happened?
怎么回事？

1101
01:35:25,920 --> 01:35:27,790
What about the pirate? Can you still see the pirate?
海盗呢？还在附近吗？

1102
01:35:28,510 --> 01:35:30,350
And the other guys? Still going out the back?
其他人呢？他们还在后撤吗？

1103
01:36:18,080 --> 01:36:20,920
（塞尔维亚语）“来自我们星球的诚挚祝愿”

1104
01:36:21,300 --> 01:36:25,790
（奥里亚语）“来自太阳系第三颗行星”

1105
01:36:25,810 --> 01:36:29,730
（奥里亚语）“地球的问候”

1106
01:36:29,780 --> 01:36:32,240
（干达语）“向宇宙所有族群致意”

1107
01:36:32,250 --> 01:36:34,340
（干达语）“愿和平永远伴随你们”

1108
01:36:34,360 --> 01:36:42,810
（马拉地语）“地球人民向你们传递美好的祝愿”

1109
01:36:43,030 --> 01:36:45,790
（台语）“太空的朋友们 你们好”

1110
01:36:46,060 --> 01:36:49,040
（台语）“吃过饭没？来我们这儿坐坐”

1111
01:36:49,090 --> 01:36:54,680
（匈牙利语）“用匈牙利语向宇宙中所有热爱和平的生命致意”

1112
01:36:55,080 --> 01:36:59,000
（泰卢固语）“说泰卢固语的人们向你们致以美好的祝愿”

1113
01:36:59,070 --> 01:37:02,190
（捷克语）“亲爱的朋友们 祝你们万事如意”

1114
01:37:02,370 --> 01:37:05,950
（卡纳达语）“代表说卡纳达语的人们 向你们致以美好祝愿”

1115
01:37:06,060 --> 01:37:10,420
（拉贾斯坦语）“大家好 我们这里很幸福”

1116
01:37:10,430 --> 01:37:12,630
（拉贾斯坦语）“愿你们那里也同样幸福”

1117
01:37:12,840 --> 01:37:15,920
"Hello from the children of planet Earth."
（英语）“来自地球儿童的问候”

1118
01:37:58,460 --> 01:37:59,990
Hello, my name is Phil.
你好 我叫菲尔

1119
01:38:02,500 --> 01:38:04,400
And you're Mary, yeah?
你是玛丽 对吧？

1120
01:38:06,340 --> 01:38:10,990
Uh... I was hoping to ask you a few questions, just for...
我想问你几个问题 主要是...

1121
01:38:13,400 --> 01:38:16,340
some clarification on our end,
为了核实一些细节

1122
01:38:16,610 --> 01:38:17,680
if that's okay.
没问题吧？

1123
01:38:23,970 --> 01:38:26,900
Uh, first thing, um...
呃 首先...

1124
01:38:26,920 --> 01:38:29,230
could you establish how you, uh...
你能说说 你是怎么...

1125
01:38:30,630 --> 01:38:31,800
got in here?
进来的吗？

1126
01:38:34,960 --> 01:38:36,460
I walked through a wall
我穿过了一堵墙

1127
01:38:37,590 --> 01:38:39,260
in the basement of a furniture store.
就在一家家具店的地下室里

1128
01:38:47,140 --> 01:38:49,780
Can you confirm that this is the location in question?
你看这张照片 是这里吧？

1129
01:38:47,420 --> 01:38:49,800
{\an8}（克船长的家具帝国）

1130
01:38:59,040 --> 01:39:01,780
Okay, good. So you were shopping, or...
好的 你当时想购物 还是...

1131
01:39:04,510 --> 01:39:06,110
I was looking for someone.
我当时在找人

1132
01:39:11,600 --> 01:39:12,510
Um...
呃...

1133
01:39:18,120 --> 01:39:19,710
were you looking for this man,
你找的那个人

1134
01:39:19,900 --> 01:39:21,300
right here?
是他吧？

1135
01:39:25,150 --> 01:39:26,450
Where am I right now?
我现在在哪？

1136
01:39:26,470 --> 01:39:28,550
Could you just confirm for me?
帮我确认一下行吗？

1137
01:39:29,120 --> 01:39:31,090
Is this man right here the man you were looking for?
这就是你要找的人吧？

1138
01:39:31,100 --> 01:39:32,350
Please.
拜托

1139
01:39:32,360 --> 01:39:33,860
- Sorry, what was your name? - Phil.
- 抱歉 你刚才说你叫什么？ - 菲尔

1140
01:39:35,960 --> 01:39:38,290
Please, Phil. Where am I?
请告诉我 菲尔 我现在在哪？

1141
01:39:39,250 --> 01:39:40,480
I'm not...
我不...

1142
01:39:47,860 --> 01:39:50,540
I make, um... Sorry, my...
我是做...呃...抱歉 我的...

1143
01:39:50,680 --> 01:39:53,010
Our company, we make...
我们的公司 是生产...

1144
01:39:54,250 --> 01:39:55,780
MRI machines.
核磁共振成像仪的

1145
01:39:54,250 --> 01:39:56,770
{\an8}（异步研究所）

1146
01:39:56,310 --> 01:39:58,550
Or... I should say, um,
或者...应该说

1147
01:39:58,570 --> 01:40:01,000
we used to make MRI machines.
我们曾经是做核磁共振仪的

1148
01:40:02,680 --> 01:40:03,800
Not anymore.
现在不再做了

1149
01:40:05,080 --> 01:40:06,340
That was before we...
那是在我们...

1150
01:40:08,900 --> 01:40:10,630
- Before we found-- - You've been there.
- 在我们发现那个.... - 你也进去过

1151
01:40:18,150 --> 01:40:20,350
Yes, I have.
是的 我去过

1152
01:40:22,660 --> 01:40:25,500
And now, it's my job.
现在这成了我的工作

1153
01:40:26,550 --> 01:40:28,280
Every day, I-I go in there
我每...每天都进去

1154
01:40:28,760 --> 01:40:30,910
and I just try to f...
试着...

1155
01:40:31,880 --> 01:40:33,840
try to find out ev-even a little bit more.
试着多弄懂一点也好

1156
01:40:34,380 --> 01:40:37,580
I-I map out areas to the best of my ability.
我在尽全力绘制地图

1157
01:40:38,180 --> 01:40:40,140
And more and more, I'm convinced
玛丽 我越来越坚信

1158
01:40:41,630 --> 01:40:45,610
that nothing in our lifetime, Mary,
在我们有生之年

1159
01:40:45,620 --> 01:40:48,930
n-nothing in-in maybe all of recorded history
甚...甚至在整个人类记录的历史中

1160
01:40:50,110 --> 01:40:53,530
means more than this.
没什么比这更重要了

1161
01:40:54,840 --> 01:40:57,100
But I don't understand it. I don't...
可我就是没搞明白

1162
01:40:57,110 --> 01:40:58,830
I-I can't even describe it.
我...我根本说不上来

1163
01:40:59,490 --> 01:41:00,520
It...
这...

1164
01:41:00,880 --> 01:41:04,560
It's like describing a dog to someone who's never seen a dog.
这就好比给个没见过狗的人形容狗

1165
01:41:05,510 --> 01:41:07,620
And then asking them to draw it.
然后让那人把狗画出来

1166
01:41:13,450 --> 01:41:16,050
Now you want me to... describe it.
现在你想让我...形容它

1167
01:41:18,650 --> 01:41:21,820
And then you'll write it down, and then what?
然后你记下来 之后呢？

1168
01:41:21,830 --> 01:41:23,780
- Mary-- - You'll let me go?
- 玛丽... - 之后我就能走了吗？

1169
01:41:23,800 --> 01:41:25,430
We all want the same thing here.
其实咱们想的一样

1170
01:41:25,450 --> 01:41:26,700
We do.
真的

1171
01:41:26,710 --> 01:41:31,210
We just want to find out even a little bit more.
咱们都只想 哪怕能多弄懂一点点

1172
01:41:32,720 --> 01:41:34,320
What's gonna happen to me, Phil?
菲尔 我最后会怎么样？

1173
01:41:40,340 --> 01:41:41,820
That decision's not up to me.
这不是我能左右的

1174
01:41:43,180 --> 01:41:44,030
So...
那...

1175
01:41:45,290 --> 01:41:48,420
if we could just talk, just you and me,
咱们能不能就简单聊聊 就咱俩

1176
01:41:49,270 --> 01:41:51,730
you know, just like... just like two regular people.
就像...就像普通人那样

1177
01:41:53,090 --> 01:41:56,090
We could unpack some of this, we've both been in there,
咱们摊开聊聊 毕竟咱俩都进去过

1178
01:41:56,100 --> 01:41:58,870
and-and-and get on the same page.
这样咱...咱们才能把话说到一块儿去

1179
01:42:00,150 --> 01:42:04,520
There are doors opening everywhere.
现在 到处都在出现开启的门

1180
01:42:05,190 --> 01:42:08,460
We don't know why or what's connecting them.
我们搞不懂是啥把这些连在一起的

1181
01:42:08,490 --> 01:42:10,640
They sort of keep happening, and...
没完没了地出现

1182
01:42:10,910 --> 01:42:13,180
and we don't know how to stop them...
我们完全不知道怎么让它停下来...

1183
01:42:43,430 --> 01:42:48,910
{\an8}（山脊公寓楼盘）

1184
